t', methodName = 'binderMapsExternalConfigurationToKafkaProperties', methodParameterTypes = '']\n332:    => org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError: Cannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public org.springframework.cloud.stream.binder.kafka.properties.KafkaBindingProperties()'.\n336:Unsatisfied runtime conditions:\n378:Test run finished after 9 ms\n380:BUILD FAILED in 42s\n390:[         9 tests successful      ]\n391:[         1 tests failed          ]\n425:BUILD FAILED in 43s\n== human-intervention-logs/org.springframework.cloud:spring-cloud-stream-binder-kafka:5.0.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-20T02-57-30-471957Z.log ==\n61:org_springframework_cloud.spring_cloud_stream_binder_kafka.Spring_cloud_stream_binder_kafkaTest > binderMapsExternalConfigurationToKafkaProperties() FAILED\n79:  JUnit Jupiter:Spring_cloud_stream_binder_kafkaTest:binderMapsExternalConfigurationToKafkaProperties()\n80:    MethodSource [className = 'org_springframework_cloud.spring_cloud_stream_binder_kafka.Spring_cloud_stream_binder_kafkaTest', methodName = 'binderMapsExternalConfigurationToKafkaProperties', methodParameterTypes = '']\n81:    => org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError: Cannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public org.springframework.cloud.stream.binder.kafka.properties.KafkaBindingProperties()'.\n85:Unsatisfied runtime conditions:\n114:Test run finished after 8 ms\n125:[         9 tests successful      ]\n126:[         1 tests failed          ]\n143:BUILD FAILED in 2s\n174:BUILD FAILED in 3s\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_24","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n 'stats/org.springframework.cloud/spring-cloud-stream-binder-kafka/5.0.1/stats.json|spring-cloud-stream-binder-kafka/5.0.1/stats.json|coverage' . .. -S\"","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_24","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n 'stats/org.springframework.cloud/spring-cloud-stream-binder-kafka/5.0.1/stats.json|spring-cloud-stream-binder-kafka/5.0.1/stats.json|coverage' . .. -S\"","aggregated_output":"./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `library-update-request` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that updates metadata/tests for an existing library version, especially generated PRs titled like `[GenAI] Improve coverage for group:artifact:version using gpt-5.5`. Focus on preserving dynamic-access coverage percentage between versions, verifying reporter-requested metadata is present and exercised by tests, and applying the relevant test/scope rules from new-library reviews without requiring a minimum new-library dynamic-access coverage threshold.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:8:These PRs update support for an existing library version. Review them as existing-library updates: the target library is already supported, so the PR must preserve coverage quality while adding any metadata or tests requested by the linked issue.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:16:- Dynamic-access coverage percentage must not drop between the previously supported version and the requested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason. Compare the percentage/ratio only; do not block because the absolute covered or total call count changed.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:17:- Do not require `library-new-request`'s minimum dynamic-access threshold. A library update can be acceptable with low coverage if the percentage did not regress and the requested issue work is covered.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:55:4. Check dynamic-access coverage percentage.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:59:   - Use `versions[0].dynamicAccess.coverageRatio` or the equivalent ratio shown in the PR description.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:61:   - A lower coverage percentage for the requested version is blocking unless the PR gives a concrete explanation, such as upstream removal of reachable dynamic-access sites or an intentionally narrower supported surface.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:64:   - Do not apply the `library-new-request` rule that dynamic-access coverage must be above 20%.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:89:   - If CI is flaky but the diff, issue-requested metadata, and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:96:- Dynamic-access coverage percentage did not drop between the previous version and requested version, or any drop is convincingly explained by an upstream surface change.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:104:- Dynamic-access coverage percentage drops without a credible explanation.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:107:- Tests use direct reflection, no-op class literals, or direct resource checks to fake requested-metadata coverage.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:122:- For coverage percentage drops: say that `library-update-request` PRs must not reduce dynamic-access coverage percentage between versions, cite old and new percentages, and ask for restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:125:- For fake requested-metadata coverage: say direct reflection/class literals/direct resource lookup prove only the test code, not the library path that needs metadata.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:136:- Bad issue-requested metadata coverage with direct reflection:\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:147:- Better issue-requested metadata coverage through public API:\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:161:- Bad resource coverage with direct lookup only:\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:173:- Better resource coverage through library initialization:\n./build.gradle:146:            \"generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport\",\n./post-gen-interventions/org.springframework.cloud_spring-cloud-stream-binder-kafka_5.0.1.md:42:The generated test suite has broad useful coverage for this library: nine native tests passed, covering Kafka binder configuration objects, header mapping, tombstone conversion, provisioning utilities, binding utilities, topic/DLQ helpers, and SpEL-based message key handling. The one failing test is also valuable because it exposes a real Spring Boot configuration-binding metadata gap for `KafkaBindingProperties`. Removing it would hide an actionable reachability metadata issue instead of documenting the remaining metadata work needed.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:8:These PRs are created by the scheduled compatibility workflow and are expected to update supported library versions by changing `metadata/**/index.json`. They may also refresh the generated root `COVERAGE.md` when tested-version changes affect the coverage table.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:14:- Approve silently when the PR only updates the expected metadata index files, optionally with generated root `COVERAGE.md`, and CI is green, then enable auto-merge.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:28:   - Expected files: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json`, plus the generated root `COVERAGE.md` when the PR updates tested versions.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:43:     - any other non-`metadata/**/index.json` file, except the generated root `COVERAGE.md`\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:48:   - A `COVERAGE.md` refresh is allowed as generated fallout from the listed library updates; it does not need to be listed as a separate library change.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:49:   - There should not be hidden updates outside the listed libraries, except the generated root `COVERAGE.md`.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:53:   - If the PR unexpectedly triggered build-logic or workflow-heavy jobs, that is a sign the diff scope is wrong. A root `COVERAGE.md` change alone is not workflow-heavy.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:92:- The PR is limited to the expected `metadata/**/index.json` files, optionally with generated root `COVERAGE.md`.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:93:- Or the PR is a pure verified pre-release promotion rename limited to the matching `metadata/`, `tests/src/`, `stats/`, `index.json`, and optional root `COVERAGE.md` changes.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-java-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR described as `fixes-java-run-fail` or one that fixes Java/JVM runtime test failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the Java runtime fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair tests, dependencies, or narrow runtime setup after an existing library version compiles, but the JVM-based test fails when it runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to restore Java runtime behavior for the new version while preserving meaningful test and dynamic-access coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:17:- Be more relaxed than `library-new-request`: do not reject only because a test resembles older coverage, stays in an existing package layout, or contains compatibility branches for multiple supported versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept changes that remove meaningful test coverage just to make `java` pass.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:60:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:61:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:71:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/runtime-surface change.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:77:   - Prefer seeing the full target `test` lane green because a Java runtime fix can still reduce native-image coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:79:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:87:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API/runtime surface.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:95:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:103:- The API or runtime behavior change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:112:- For deleted or bypassed coverage: say that the PR fixes Java runtime execution by removing coverage and should instead adapt the test to the new runtime behavior.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:114:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:21:- Require reported dynamic-access coverage above 20% when there are dynamic-access calls to cover. Use the exploded stats files under `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` when available, and block the PR when dynamic-access coverage is 20% or lower or the PR provides no credible dynamic-access coverage evidence for non-zero dynamic-access calls.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:22:- Treat dynamic-access coverage counts as a minimum gate, not complete metadata evidence. They can miss metadata required through downstream libraries, so do not use high coverage alone to prove that the submitted metadata is complete or necessary.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:23:- Treat `0/0` dynamic-access coverage as a valid no-calls case, not as failed coverage. Do not reject a PR only because the exploded stats report `0/0` dynamic-access calls while the PR adds metadata; those stats can miss metadata required through downstream libraries.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:61:5. Compare the PR claims, test, and reported coverage as one unit.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:62:   - If the PR claims specific coverage numbers that do not line up with the diff, ask for investigation.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:63:   - Confirm reported dynamic-access coverage is above 20% when the stats include dynamic-access calls.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:66:   - If the stats report 20% coverage or lower for non-zero dynamic-access calls, or no usable coverage signal for claimed dynamic-access behavior, ask for stronger tests or refreshed coverage evidence.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:67:   - Ask for metadata/coverage mismatch investigation only when the covered dynamic-access call count is at least 75% higher than the PR-reported metadata entry count, where the reported count is `Metadata entries` plus `Test-only metadata entries` when both are present. For older PRs, use legacy `Entries` or `Entries found` as the metadata entry count.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:90:  - Reported dynamic-access coverage is 20% or lower for non-zero dynamic-access calls, absent for claimed dynamic-access behavior, or not credible from the diff.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:97:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:101:- For insufficient dynamic-access coverage: say that new-library PRs need dynamic-access coverage above 20% when there are dynamic-access calls to cover, and ask for stronger tests or refreshed coverage evidence.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:102:- For unsupported coverage claims: ask for refreshed coverage evidence when the PR makes concrete coverage claims that are not supported by the diff.\n./skills/README.md:22:It covers new-library metadata PRs, including titles like `[GenAI] Add support for com.fasterxml:classmate:1.5.1 using gpt-5.4`, and encodes the review rules already used in this repository: reject scaffold-only tests, keep test packages separate from library packages so tests do not bypass visibility boundaries, and question metadata coverage claims that are not supported by the diff.\n./skills/README.md:27:It covers compile-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the compile fix, preserve meaningful tests, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:32:It covers JVM runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the Java runtime fix, preserve meaningful tests and assertions, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:37:It covers native-image runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: verify the native path is fixed rather than skipped, keep metadata and test changes scoped, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./COVERAGE.md:1:# Coverage\n./COVERAGE.md:5:![Coverage over Time](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/stats/coverage/latest/metrics-over-time.svg#gh-light-mode-only)\n./COVERAGE.md:6:![Coverage over Time](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/stats/coverage/latest/metrics-over-time-dark.svg#gh-dark-mode-only)\n./COVERAGE.md:10:| Library | Versions | Description | Dynamic access coverage |\n./COVERAGE.md:1169:| `org.scoverage:scalac-scoverage-runtime_2.13` | [1.4.1<br>- 2.5.2](metadata/org.scoverage/scalac-scoverage-runtime_2.13/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> scalac-scoverage-runtime provides the runtime support used by the scoverage Scala compiler plugin to record coverage measurements from instrumented Scala code. It writes and reads invoked statement identifiers so scoverage can calculate statement and branch coverage after tests run.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/org.scoverage/scalac-scoverage-runtime_2.13/) |\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:53:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:55:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - If metadata fixes make the native run pass but the dynamic-access ratio drops, ask for restored coverage first. Passing native execution is not enough by itself.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:76:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:84:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:90:- The fix makes native execution pass by skipping the failing native path, disabling assertions, or removing coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:91:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:100:- The API or native runtime change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:109:- For native skips: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair test sources or test dependencies after an existing library is bumped and the new version no longer compiles with the old test code. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to preserve working coverage across the version update rather than prove a brand-new metadata contribution from scratch.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:17:- Be more relaxed than `library-new-request`: do not reject only because a test resembles older coverage, stays in an existing package layout, or contains compatibility branches for multiple supported versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept changes that remove meaningful test coverage just to make `javac` pass.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:54:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:74:   - Prefer seeing the full target `test` lane green because a compile fix can still reduce runtime or native coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:76:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:84:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:90:- The fix makes compilation pass by weakening or bypassing the test instead of adapting it to the changed API while preserving meaningful coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:92:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:100:- The API change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:109:- For deleted coverage: say that the PR fixes compilation by removing coverage and should instead adapt the test to the new API.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:121:- Bad compile repair that removes coverage:\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `library-update-request` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that updates metadata/tests for an existing library version, especially generated PRs titled like `[GenAI] Improve coverage for group:artifact:version using gpt-5.5`. Focus on preserving dynamic-access coverage percentage between versions, verifying reporter-requested metadata is present and exercised by tests, and applying the relevant test/scope rules from new-library reviews without requiring a minimum new-library dynamic-access coverage threshold.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:8:These PRs update support for an existing library version. Review them as existing-library updates: the target library is already supported, so the PR must preserve coverage quality while adding any metadata or tests requested by the linked issue.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:16:- Dynamic-access coverage percentage must not drop between the previously supported version and the requested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason. Compare the percentage/ratio only; do not block because the absolute covered or total call count changed.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:17:- Do not require `library-new-request`'s minimum dynamic-access threshold. A library update can be acceptable with low coverage if the percentage did not regress and the requested issue work is covered.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:55:4. Check dynamic-access coverage percentage.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:59:   - Use `versions[0].dynamicAccess.coverageRatio` or the equivalent ratio shown in the PR description.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:61:   - A lower coverage percentage for the requested version is blocking unless the PR gives a concrete explanation, such as upstream removal of reachable dynamic-access sites or an intentionally narrower supported surface.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:64:   - Do not apply the `library-new-request` rule that dynamic-access coverage must be above 20%.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:89:   - If CI is flaky but the diff, issue-requested metadata, and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:96:- Dynamic-access coverage percentage did not drop between the previous version and requested version, or any drop is convincingly explained by an upstream surface change.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:104:- Dynamic-access coverage percentage drops without a credible explanation.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:107:- Tests use direct reflection, no-op class literals, or direct resource checks to fake requested-metadata coverage.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:122:- For coverage percentage drops: say that `library-update-request` PRs must not reduce dynamic-access coverage percentage between versions, cite old and new percentages, and ask for restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:125:- For fake requested-metadata coverage: say direct reflection/class literals/direct resource lookup prove only the test code, not the library path that needs metadata.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:136:- Bad issue-requested metadata coverage with direct reflection:\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:147:- Better issue-requested metadata coverage through public API:\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:161:- Bad resource coverage with direct lookup only:\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:173:- Better resource coverage through library initialization:\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:54:from ai_workflows.improve_library_coverage import (\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:55:    main as run_improve_library_coverage_workflow,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:78:from git_scripts.make_pr_improve_coverage import main as run_make_pr_improve_coverage\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:79:from utility_scripts.dynamic_access_report import load_dynamic_access_coverage_report\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:202:LOW_DYNAMIC_ACCESS_COVERAGE_RATIO = 0.10\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:303:class DynamicAccessCoverageSnapshot:\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:306:    coverage_ratio: float\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:314:    coverage: DynamicAccessCoverageSnapshot | None = None\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:315:    reason: str = \"low_dynamic_access_coverage\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2522:def _load_dynamic_access_snapshot_from_metrics(run_metrics: dict | None) -> DynamicAccessCoverageSnapshot | None:\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2523:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\"\"\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2540:    coverage_ratio = dynamic_access.get(\"coverageRatio\")\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2541:    if c