orge_metadata.py:3576:            \"improve-coverage-workflow\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3577:            f\"Invoking improve_library_coverage workflow for issue #{issue_number}: \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3591:        rc = run_improve_library_coverage_workflow(pipeline_argv)\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3597:                f\"ERROR: improve_library_coverage workflow failed for issue #{issue_number} (exit {rc})\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4449:        run_make_pr_improve_coverage(\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5676:            \"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:390:    \"name\": \"javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.4\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:391:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: runs javac_iterative to fix compilation, then improves dynamic-access coverage.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:393:    \"workflow\": \"increase_dynamic_access_coverage\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:412:    \"name\": \"javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:413:    \"description\": \"Same configuration as javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.4, but uses gpt-5.5 instead.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:415:    \"workflow\": \"increase_dynamic_access_coverage\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:435:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: optimistic bulk DA coverage, then per-class DA refinement.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:437:    \"workflow\": \"increase_dynamic_access_coverage\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:474:    \"name\": \"java_run_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:475:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: runs java_run_iterative to fix runtime failures, then improves dynamic-access coverage.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:477:    \"workflow\": \"increase_dynamic_access_coverage\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:533:    \"description\": \"Pi bulk dynamic-access strategy. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, which iterates through uncovered classes and refines coverage class by class, this strategy gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one prompt and asks it to cover the missing accesses in a single broad pass.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:552:    \"description\": \"Codex bulk dynamic-access strategy. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, which iterates through uncovered classes and refines coverage class by class, this strategy gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one prompt and asks it to cover the missing accesses in a single broad pass.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:611:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: optimistic bulk DA coverage, then per-class DA refinement.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:613:    \"workflow\": \"increase_dynamic_access_coverage\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:634:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: optimistic bulk DA coverage, then per-class DA refinement using gpt-5.5.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:636:    \"workflow\": \"increase_dynamic_access_coverage\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:657:    \"description\": \"Composite Codex strategy: optimistic bulk DA coverage, then per-class DA refinement.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:659:    \"workflow\": \"increase_dynamic_access_coverage\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:680:    \"description\": \"Composite Codex strategy: optimistic bulk DA coverage, then per-class DA refinement using gpt-5.5.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:682:    \"workflow\": \"increase_dynamic_access_coverage\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:759:    \"description\": \"Library-update strategy: skips primary workflow, directly runs dynamic-access coverage improvement on existing tests.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:761:    \"workflow\": \"increase_dynamic_access_coverage\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:799:    \"description\": \"Library-update composite strategy: bulk dynamic-access coverage in one broad pass first, then per-class iterative refinement of any stragglers. Mirrors the iterative library-update strategy but starts with a faster bulk pass.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:801:    \"workflow\": \"increase_dynamic_access_coverage\",\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateReadmeBadgeSummaryTask.java:36:        ReadmeBadgeSummarySupport.writeCoverageMarkdown(\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateReadmeBadgeSummaryTask.java:37:                getCoverageMarkdownFile(),\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:57:The harness uses a single coordinates filter `-Pcoordinates=` accepting `all`, `group:artifact`, `group:artifact:version`, or shard `k/n`. It also exposes authoring helpers (`generateMetadata`, `splitTestOnlyMetadata`, `fixTestNativeImageRun`, `addTestedVersion`, `fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`), reporting tasks (`jacocoTestReport`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `generateLibraryStats`, `analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess`), and the `package` release task. The full task reference lives in [DEVELOPING.md](DEVELOPING.md).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:63:- Schedule-driven: full metadata sweep every three days to prevent incomplete or breaking metadata from shipping in releases, new-library-version compatibility (every six hours), Docker image vulnerability scans, scheduled release every two weeks, scheduled coverage publication.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:71:### 4.5 Coverage and metrics dashboard\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:73:`publish-scheduled-coverage.yml` derives, from committed `stats/` and `metadata/**/index.json`:\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:75:- `COVERAGE.md` — the per-library coverage table linked from the README. Each\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:77:  `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json` file and the dynamic-access coverage\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:79:- `latest/metrics-over-time.svg` and `latest/metrics-over-time-dark.svg` — light and dark historical charts referenced from [COVERAGE.md](../COVERAGE.md).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:82:CI must keep the root [COVERAGE.md](../COVERAGE.md) on the source branch in\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:83:sync with the generated coverage table through the bulk-update PRs created by\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:`verify-new-library-version-compatibility.yml`. The same `COVERAGE.md` and the\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:85:badge, graph, and history artifacts are published to the `stats/coverage` branch.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:93:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:104:| `library-update-request` | Issue / PR | Request or PR to improve support for an already-covered library, including coverage-improvement work. |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:223:- **FR-T-7** Dynamic-access coverage between consecutive tested versions of a library must not regress (enforced by reviewer skills `review-fixes-javac-fail`, `review-fixes-native-image-run-fail`, `review-fixes-java-run-fail`).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:263:- **NFR-7 Auditability.** Every Forge run produces a schema-validated metrics record; every coverage publish writes to a force-pushed branch with retained history.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:278:- Mirrored stats under `stats/`, a generated root `COVERAGE.md`, and aggregated coverage artifacts on `stats/coverage`.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:8:These PRs are created by the scheduled compatibility workflow and are expected to update supported library versions by changing `metadata/**/index.json`. They may also refresh the generated root `COVERAGE.md` when tested-version changes affect the coverage table.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:14:- Approve silently when the PR only updates the expected metadata index files, optionally with generated root `COVERAGE.md`, and CI is green, then enable auto-merge.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:28:   - Expected files: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json`, plus the generated root `COVERAGE.md` when the PR updates tested versions.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:43:     - any other non-`metadata/**/index.json` file, except the generated root `COVERAGE.md`\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:48:   - A `COVERAGE.md` refresh is allowed as generated fallout from the listed library updates; it does not need to be listed as a separate library change.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:49:   - There should not be hidden updates outside the listed libraries, except the generated root `COVERAGE.md`.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:53:   - If the PR unexpectedly triggered build-logic or workflow-heavy jobs, that is a sign the diff scope is wrong. A root `COVERAGE.md` change alone is not workflow-heavy.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:92:- The PR is limited to the expected `metadata/**/index.json` files, optionally with generated root `COVERAGE.md`.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:93:- Or the PR is a pure verified pre-release promotion rename limited to the matching `metadata/`, `tests/src/`, `stats/`, `index.json`, and optional root `COVERAGE.md` changes.\n./docs/CI.md:40:  - Uses: [`fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) plus [`generateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to build a [`ci.json`](../ci.json)-driven matrix. The matrix generator limits the number of libraries per run, limits each library to at most 30 newer versions per run before expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, records tested versions only after they pass on every required environment, refreshes root [COVERAGE.md](../COVERAGE.md) in the generated bulk-update PR, and creates a single aggregated failure issue per failed library version while preserving the prior failure issue format with added OS and JDK lines.\n./docs/CI.md:46:- [.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml](../.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml): scheduled/manual workflow that generates repository coverage badges and the coverage dashboard from exploded stats files under [stats/](../stats/) and repository [metadata/**/index.json](../metadata/), then force-pushes the published artifacts to the `stats/coverage` branch. The published branch only keeps `COVERAGE.md`, `latest/badges.json`, `latest/metrics-over-time.svg`, `latest/metrics-over-time-dark.svg`, and `history/history.json`.\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:119:    code_coverage_percent = metrics.get(\"code_coverage_percent\", 0)\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:122:    previous_library_coverage_percent = metrics.get(\"previous_library_coverage_percent\", 0)\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:151:- Library coverage percentage: {code_coverage_percent}\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:154:- Previous library version coverage percentage: {previous_library_coverage_percent}\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py:13:    [--strategy-name \"java_run_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\"] \\\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-java-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR described as `fixes-java-run-fail` or one that fixes Java/JVM runtime test failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the Java runtime fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair tests, dependencies, or narrow runtime setup after an existing library version compiles, but the JVM-based test fails when it runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to restore Java runtime behavior for the new version while preserving meaningful test and dynamic-access coverage.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:17:- Be more relaxed than `library-new-request`: do not reject only because a test resembles older coverage, stays in an existing package layout, or contains compatibility branches for multiple supported versions.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept changes that remove meaningful test coverage just to make `java` pass.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:60:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:61:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:71:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/runtime-surface change.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:77:   - Prefer seeing the full target `test` lane green because a Java runtime fix can still reduce native-image coverage.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:79:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:87:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API/runtime surface.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:95:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:103:- The API or runtime behavior change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:112:- For deleted or bypassed coverage: say that the PR fixes Java runtime execution by removing coverage and should instead adapt the test to the new runtime behavior.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:114:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AbstractLibraryStatsTask.java:88:    protected Set<StatsLocation> metadataVersionsWithCompleteCoverage(Collection<String> coordinates) {\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AbstractLibraryStatsTask.java:200:    protected Path getDynamicAccessCoverageReport(String coordinates) {\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AbstractLibraryStatsTask.java:205:                .resolve(\"dynamic-access-coverage.json\");\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AbstractLibraryStatsTask.java:212:        // to instrument and produces no report. Keep coverage as N/A, but model\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AbstractLibraryStatsTask.java:216:                    \"Library JARs for {} contain no bytecode. Writing empty dynamic access stats and N/A coverage.\",\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AbstractLibraryStatsTask.java:222:                    LibraryStatsSupport.unavailableLibraryCoverage()\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:27:    collect_version_coverage_metrics,\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:161:    previous_coverage, _ = collect_version_coverage_metrics(repo_path, group, artifact, old_version)\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:162:    new_coverage, _ = collect_version_coverage_metrics(repo_path, group, artifact, new_version)\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:182:        f\"- Library coverage (previous): {previous_coverage:.2f}%\\n\"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:183:        f\"- Library coverage (new): {new_coverage:.2f}%\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/java_fail_workflow.py:40:DEFAULT_JAVAC_STRATEGY = \"javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/java_fail_workflow.py:41:DEFAULT_JAVA_RUN_STRATEGY = \"java_run_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\"\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:21:- Require reported dynamic-access coverage above 20% when there are dynamic-access calls to cover. Use the exploded stats files under `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` when available, and block the PR when dynamic-access coverage is 20% or lower or the PR provides no credible dynamic-access coverage evidence for non-zero dynamic-access calls.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:22:- Treat dynamic-access coverage counts as a minimum gate, not complete metadata evidence. They can miss metadata required through downstream libraries, so do not use high coverage alone to prove that the submitted metadata is complete or necessary.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:23:- Treat `0/0` dynamic-access coverage as a valid no-calls case, not as failed coverage. Do not reject a PR only because the exploded stats report `0/0` dynamic-access calls while the PR adds metadata; those stats can miss metadata required through downstream libraries.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:61:5. Compare the PR claims, test, and reported coverage as one unit.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:62:   - If the PR claims specific coverage numbers that do not line up with the diff, ask for investigation.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:63:   - Confirm reported dynamic-access coverage is above 20% when the stats include dynamic-access calls.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:66:   - If the stats report 20% coverage or lower for non-zero dynamic-access calls, or no usable coverage signal for claimed dynamic-access behavior, ask for stronger tests or refreshed coverage evidence.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:67:   - Ask for metadata/coverage mismatch investigation only when the covered dynamic-access call count is at least 75% higher than the PR-reported metadata entry count, where the reported count is `Metadata entries` plus `Test-only metadata entries` when both are present. For older PRs, use legacy `Entries` or `Entries found` as the metadata entry count.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:90:  - Reported dynamic-access coverage is 20% or lower for non-zero dynamic-access calls, absent for claimed dynamic-access behavior, or not credible from the diff.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:97:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:101:- For insufficient dynamic-access coverage: say that new-library PRs need dynamic-access coverage above 20% when there are dynamic-access calls to cover, and ask for stronger tests or refreshed coverage evidence.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:102:- For unsupported coverage claims: ask for refreshed coverage evidence when the PR makes concrete coverage claims that are not supported by the diff.\n./forge/utility_scripts/jacoco_parser.py:7:JaCoCo XML coverage parser.\n./forge/utility_scripts/jacoco_parser.py:8:Parses lines coverage from JaCoCo XML and aggregates all <counter type='LINE'> elements.\n./forge/utility_scripts/jacoco_parser.py:19:def compute_line_coverage(xml_path: str):\n./forge/utility_scripts/jacoco_parser.py:21:    Aggregate line counters from a JaCoCo XML report and return coverage percent.\n./forge/utility_scripts/jacoco_parser.py:57:    percent, cov