({coverage_percent:.2f}%) from {candidate.coverage.source}\"\n../7031-83b3a4c4/forge/forge_metadata.py:2857:        f\"{coverage_details}\\n\\n\"\n../7031-83b3a4c4/forge/forge_metadata.py:3424:            coverage=None,\n../7031-83b3a4c4/forge/forge_metadata.py:3576:            \"improve-coverage-workflow\",\n../7031-83b3a4c4/forge/forge_metadata.py:3577:            f\"Invoking improve_library_coverage workflow for issue #{issue_number}: \"\n../7031-83b3a4c4/forge/forge_metadata.py:3591:        rc = run_improve_library_coverage_workflow(pipeline_argv)\n../7031-83b3a4c4/forge/forge_metadata.py:3597:                f\"ERROR: improve_library_coverage workflow failed for issue #{issue_number} (exit {rc})\",\n../7031-83b3a4c4/forge/forge_metadata.py:4449:        run_make_pr_improve_coverage(\n../7031-83b3a4c4/forge/forge_metadata.py:5676:            \"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\"\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/README.md:22:It covers new-library metadata PRs, including titles like `[GenAI] Add support for com.fasterxml:classmate:1.5.1 using gpt-5.4`, and encodes the review rules already used in this repository: reject scaffold-only tests, keep test packages separate from library packages so tests do not bypass visibility boundaries, and question metadata coverage claims that are not supported by the diff.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/README.md:27:It covers compile-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the compile fix, preserve meaningful tests, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/README.md:32:It covers JVM runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the Java runtime fix, preserve meaningful tests and assertions, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/README.md:37:It covers native-image runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: verify the native path is fixed rather than skipped, keep metadata and test changes scoped, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:37:from utility_scripts.dynamic_access_report import DynamicAccessCallSite, load_dynamic_access_coverage_report\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:126:        \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:150:    report = load_dynamic_access_coverage_report(report_path)\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:153:        for class_coverage in report.classes\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:154:        for call_site in class_coverage.call_sites\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:282:    code_coverage_percent = metrics.get(\"code_coverage_percent\", 0)\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:314:- Library coverage percentage: {code_coverage_percent}\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py:279:        # Full CI-matrix GraalVM coverage, including GRAALVM_HOME_25_0, runs in\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:53:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:55:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - If metadata fixes make the native run pass but the dynamic-access ratio drops, ask for restored coverage first. Passing native execution is not enough by itself.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:76:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:84:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:90:- The fix makes native execution pass by skipping the failing native path, disabling assertions, or removing coverage.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:91:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:100:- The API or native runtime change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:109:- For native skips: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:15:@WorkflowStrategy.register(\"increase_dynamic_access_coverage\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:16:class IncreaseDynamicAccessCoverageStrategy(WorkflowStrategy):\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:17:    \"\"\"Composite strategy that runs a primary workflow then improves dynamic-access coverag