).getSession(\"coverage\", \"example.test\", 22);\n./tests/src/com.github.mwiede/jsch/2.27.7/src/test/java/com_github_mwiede/jsch/DHXECKEMTest.java:45:        Session session = new JSch().getSession(\"coverage\", \"example.test\", 22);\n./tests/src/com.github.mwiede/jsch/2.27.7/src/test/java/com_github_mwiede/jsch/DHXECKEMTest.java:122:                \"SSH-2.0-jsch-dhxeckem-coverage\\r\\n\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII));\n./tests/src/com.github.mwiede/jsch/2.27.7/src/test/java/com_github_mwiede/jsch/HostKeyTest.java:20:            \"coverage host key material\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n./tests/src/com.github.mwiede/jsch/2.27.7/src/test/java/com_github_mwiede/jsch/HostKeyTest.java:27:            HostKey hostKey = new HostKey(\"example.test\", HostKey.SSHRSA, HOST_KEY, \"coverage\");\n./tests/src/com.github.mwiede/jsch/2.27.7/src/test/java/com_github_mwiede/jsch/HostKeyTest.java:34:            assertThat(hostKey.getComment()).isEqualTo(\"coverage\");\n./tests/src/com.github.mwiede/jsch/2.27.7/src/test/java/com_github_mwiede/jsch/DHGEXTest.java:37:        Session session = new JSch().getSession(\"coverage\", \"example.test\", 22);\n./tests/src/com.github.mwiede/jsch/2.27.7/src/test/java/com_github_mwiede/jsch/DHGEXTest.java:122:                \"SSH-2.0-jsch-dhgex-coverage\\r\\n\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII));\n./tests/src/com.github.mwiede/jsch/2.27.7/src/test/java/com_github_mwiede/jsch/KeyExchangeTest.java:115:        return new JSch().getSession(\"coverage\", \"example.test\", 22);\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:57:The harness uses a single coordinates filter `-Pcoordinates=` accepting `all`, `group:artifact`, `group:artifact:version`, or shard `k/n`. It also exposes authoring helpers (`generateMetadata`, `splitTestOnlyMetadata`, `fixTestNativeImageRun`, `addTestedVersion`, `fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`), reporting tasks (`jacocoTestReport`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `generateLibraryStats`, `analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess`), and the `package` release task. The full task reference lives in [DEVELOPING.md](DEVELOPING.md).\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:63:- Schedule-driven: full metadata sweep every three days to prevent incomplete or breaking metadata from shipping in releases, new-library-version compatibility (every six hours), Docker image vulnerability scans, scheduled release every two weeks, scheduled coverage publication.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:71:### 4.5 Coverage and metrics dashboard\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:73:`publish-scheduled-coverage.yml` derives, from committed `stats/` and `metadata/**/index.json`:\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:75:- `COVERAGE.md` — the per-library coverage table linked from the README. Each\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:77:  `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json` file and the dynamic-access coverage\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:79:- `latest/metrics-over-time.svg` and `latest/metrics-over-time-dark.svg` — light and dark historical charts referenced from [COVERAGE.md](../COVERAGE.md).\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:82:CI must keep the root [COVERAGE.md](../COVERAGE.md) on the source branch in\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:83:sync with the generated coverage table through the bulk-update PRs created by\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:`verify-new-library-version-compatibility.yml`. The same `COVERAGE.md` and the\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:85:badge, graph, and history artifacts are published to the `stats/coverage` branch.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:93:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:104:| `library-update-request` | Issue / PR | Request or PR to improve support for an already-covered library, including coverage-improvement work. |\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:223:- **FR-T-7** Dynamic-access coverage between consecutive tested versions of a library must not regress (enforced by reviewer skills `review-fixes-javac-fail`, `review-fixes-native-image-run-fail`, `review-fixes-java-run-fail`).\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:263:- **NFR-7 Auditability.** Every Forge run produces a schema-validated metrics record; every coverage publish writes to a force-pushed branch with retained history.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:278:- Mirrored stats under `stats/`, a generated root `COVERAGE.md`, and aggregated coverage artifacts on `stats/coverage`.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/tests/src/com.google.api.grpc/proto-google-cloud-firestore-v1/3.31.6/src/test/java/com_google_api_grpc/proto_google_cloud_firestore_v1/Proto_google_cloud_firestore_v1Test.java:474:                .putLabels(\"purpose\", \"coverage\")\n../7031-83b3a4c4/tests/src/com.google.api.grpc/proto-google-cloud-firestore-v1/3.31.6/src/test/java/com_google_api_grpc/proto_google_cloud_firestore_v1/Proto_google_cloud_firestore_v1Test.java:501:        assertThat(addTargetRequest.getLabelsMap()).containsEntry(\"purpose\", \"coverage\");\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/CI.md:40:  - Uses: [`fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) plus [`generateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to build a [`ci.json`](../ci.json)-driven matrix. The matrix generator limits the number of libraries per run, limits each library to at most 30 newer versions per run before expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, records tested versions only after they pass on every required environment, refreshes root [COVERAGE.md](../COVERAGE.md) in the generated bulk-update PR, and creates a single aggregated failure issue per failed library version while preserving the prior failure issue format with added OS and JDK lines.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/CI.md:46:- [.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml](../.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml): scheduled/manual workflow that generates repository coverage badges and the coverage dashboard from exploded stats files under [stats/](../stats/) and repository [metadata/**/index.json](../metadata/), then force-pushes the published artifacts to the `stats/coverage` branch. The published branch only keeps `COVERAGE.md`, `latest/badges.json`, `latest/metrics-over-time.svg`, `latest/metrics-over-time-dark.svg`, and `history/history.json`.\n./tests/src/org.jvnet.staxex/stax-ex/1.8.2/src/test/java/org_jvnet_staxex/stax_ex/Stax_exTest.java:129:        byte[] payload = \"Base64EncoderStream boundary coverage\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n./tests/src/org.jvnet.staxex/stax-ex/2.0.0/src/test/java/org_jvnet_staxex/stax_ex/Stax_exTest.java:129:        byte[] payload = \"Base64EncoderStream boundary coverage\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n./tests/src/org.jvnet.staxex/stax-ex/1.8/src/test/java/org_jvnet_staxex/stax_ex/Stax_exTest.java:129:        byte[] payload = \"Base64EncoderStream boundary coverage\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/DEVELOPING.md:29:To run the same coverage with future defaults enabled:\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/DEVELOPING.md:143:### Coverage (JaCoCo)\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/DEVELOPING.md:145:Generate coverage for the library under test exercised by our tests. Report contains coverage that focus exclusively on the provided library JARs, excluding unrelated external dependencies.\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/DEVELOPING.md:318:- Generate dynamic access coverage report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/DEVELOPING.md:319:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\n../7031-83b3a4c4/docs/DEVELOPING.md:321:- Coverage (single lib): `./gradlew jacocoTes